text: OPEN HOUSE SATURDAY 03.08 FROM 1-4 PM! This fully renovated 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home in Grapevine offers modern living on a spacious half-acre lot. The home features a thoughtfully designed, functional floorplan with luxury vinyl plank flooring throughout, an abundance of natural light, and contemporary fixtures in every room. The neutral color palette complements any style and provides a welcoming atmosphere. The chef's kitchen is a standout, showcasing an oversized center island, sleek Quartz countertops, a stylish backsplash, and top-of-the-line stainless steel appliances. The master suite is a true retreat, offering a beautifully remodeled attached bathroom with a large walk-in shower. The guest bathroom is equally impressive, boasting the same modern counters and cabinetry as the kitchen for a seamless, cohesive design. In addition to the well-appointed living spaces, the home includes a versatile flex room, perfect for use as a dining area, game room, or home office. Step outside to the large covered deck, ideal for relaxing or entertaining, with views of the expansive backyard and a sizable storage shed. Located in the heart of Grapevine, this home is within walking distance of top-rated schools and is just minutes from fantastic shopping, dining, and entertainment options. With easy access to major roads and freeways, plus the airport, this is an ideal location for those seeking convenience and community in one of the most desirable areas of the DFW metroplex. Don't miss out on this stunning, move-in-ready home!

At this stunning residence with a refreshing pool, ideally positioned in the heart of the DFW metroplex, coming home feels like a vacation. Boasting nearly 4, 000 sq ft of thoughtfully curated design, this home features 4 spacious bedrooms, a handsome executive office tucked behind french doors upon entry, an elegant dining space perfect for hosting family gatherings, a beautifully renovated kitchen equipped with everything a culinary expert could desire, and upstairs game and media rooms for added enjoyment and convenience. Located in the highly sought-after Grapevine-Colleyville ISD and just minutes from historic downtown Grapevine, Lake Grapevine, DFW Airport, countless shopping and dining options, and with easy access to major thoroughfares, this home is truly a rare find.

text: Within walking distance of Grapevine Lake, this stunning and impeccable executive home has it all. Located on a large, heavily treed lot in sought-after Grapevine Colleyville ISD's Hidden Lake Estates, the sprawling property boasts a grand entry foyer open to the second floor, gleaming hardwood floors, and spacious living and formal dining rooms. The centerpiece of the home is the huge family room with a gas fireplace. The open and bright floor plan has tons of upgrades, including extensive custom millwork and vaulted or trayed ceilings in most rooms. The home offers a large kitchen that opens to the casual dining space and family room. It features granite counters, ample solid wood cabinets, glass doors, a center island, double ovens, a gas cooktop, and stainless steel appliances. A secondary bedroom and stately half bath complete the first floor. The owner's suite is private and spa-like, with tons of space in the bedroom, bath, and closet, including a sizeable seamless glass walk-in shower, corner jetted tub, and split vanities. Also upstairs is room for entertaining, play, and relaxation with a giant game room, the third and fourth bedrooms, and a full bath with two sinks. The massive backyard has an extended stamped concrete patio lined with stone accent walls, professional landscaping, and plenty of room for a pool. Updates include AC unit, interior paint throughout, refinished kitchen cabinets, and additional backyard landscaping. No carpet in the home.

text: Welcome to the Millican House, a one-of-a-kind luxury home in the Historic District, walking distance from Main Street. Originally built in 1935 as a Sears kit house, this property has been carefully preserved and rebuilt into an approximately 3, 935 square foot masterpiece. The current homeowners have thoughtfully preserved portions of the original house, adding to the charm and character of this stunning home. This property boasts four bedrooms and four bathrooms, providing ample space for comfortable living. The primary bedroom, study and an open floor plan built for entertaining are all conveniently located on the first floor. The guest house features a living area, bathroom and bedroom, perfect for hosting guests or as a private retreat. Venture outside and enjoy the refreshing cocktail pool, outdoor kitchen and living center, surrounded by plenty of lawn space for play. With its prime location in the Historic District, this property offers a unique opportunity to own a piece of history while enjoying modern amenities and comforts. We invite you to come and see this stunning property for yourself. Welcome home!

text: Located within walking distance of Main Street, the landmarked Harrison House is a traditional charmer that looks as if it was built in the 1940s but was custom built in 2017 to mirror the original house. The luxurious interior features open concept living & every detail was carefully selected with a thoughtful eye for design & lifestyle. With most of the bedrooms and living space on the first floor, including a 2nd Primary-In Law Suite with seperate entrance, this house was designed to age in place or have plenty of private space for family or guests. Another unique feature is the Solarium with double paned glass pocketdoors that is nestled between the Great Room and Kitchen. Outdoors, enjoy a low maintenance, yet stunning private garden. You must see this special house to appreciate it!

text: Foundation work to be completed with a lifetime warranty Discover the epitome of comfort & elegance in this stunning townhome nestled in Grapevine, TX. As you step inside, you'll immediately feel the warmth & charm that makes this home a true haven. Boasting thoughtful upgrades such as a brand-new range, dishwasher, & microwave. The layout is perfectly designed for both privacy & socializing. It features 2 bedrooms, thoughtfully split to ensure personal space. The open dining and living area, complete with a cozy wood-burning fireplace & an inviting wet bar, creates an ideal environment for entertaining guests or a quiet evening at home. On the 2 floor find yourself in a private sanctuary that is the primary bedroom. This spacious retreat includes 2 walk-in closets & ensuite bathroom! Situated in an enviable location, this home is just moments away from the serene Grapevine Lake & a few blocks from the vibrant historic downtown Main Street.

Beautiful large David Weekley home in desirable Silver Lakes Estates. This home is the model plan & has every sf option that could be added including, bonus room over garage, super utility, media room & 5th bedroom. Upgraded curb appeal plus thoughtful design throughout make this a perfect home. The large bright living room features a fireplace with custom wood mantle to the second floor. The living area flows to the kitchen featuring granite, SS appliances including a warming drawer. The dedicated private office features French doors with a transom, floor to ceiling custom bookshelves & woodwork. Upstairs has many options with 3 bedrooms, a media room and a oversized bonus room with built in seating and storage. Exemplary Grapevine Colleyville ISD schools. Fantastic location located within walking distance to historic downtown and lake Grapevine. Ease of access to shopping, dining, DFW airport.

This lot is the perfect place to build your dream home and create a lifetime of memories.

text: Welcome to the GE Hurst Historical House originally built in 1910. This home was extensively renovated and added on to in 2018 and is the essence of Grapevine historic living. It is situated on .54 acres with many native trees and a 960 sq ft garage workshop that has the look of an original barn. The house has over 4560 sq ft under roof and 2780 sq ft of living space. Many of the original features and trim work were preserved while fully updating the complete house and structure with all the modern top amenities. The renovated structure was rebuilt on top of a steel pier and beam foundation. The primary bedroom and guest suit along with the primary living areas are all located downstairs, while the upstairs has two additional bedrooms with full baths, a living area, and unique spacious office. The home has a porte-cochere near the mud room and laundry for easy entrance. Seller is a relative of listing agent.
